        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 3:05AM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 305 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Girard, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsburg, Frontenac, Girard, Arma, Cherokee, Weir, Chicopee,
Mindenmines, Franklin, Beulah, Opolis, Greenbush, Yale, Ringo, Lone
Oak, Brazilton, and Polk.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern Kansas...and southwestern Missouri.</instruction>
